    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A script developed in Luxeuil, in Burgundy, which was a particularly important center in the development of a Merovingian cursive style during the 7th and 8th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
